description: Yoshida & Co. has been manufacturing bags with a commitment to ""Japan Made"" ever since its establishment in 1951. Porter, branded in 1962, is the main brand of Yoshida & Co., Ltd. The name of the brand is taken from a ""porter"" who carries bags in a hotel. The founder Kichizo Yoshida\'s philosophy ""One stitch all soul"" has become their corporate motto. It describes the dedication to excellence in every stage of the manufacturing process, from design and material selection, to sewing. Porter Flex is a packable series made of nylon ripstop fabric. Foldable and light, the Flex 2Way Duffle Bag is suitable for everyday use, travel and outdoor activities. Nylon ripstop fabric aka parachute cloth is used, which has a ripstop effect from its plaid pattern woven with a thick nylon yarn. Since it prevents a whole from being expanded further, the fabric is commonly used for military ponchos and outdoor clothing. Retroreflective fabric is used for the PORTER name tag.

name: New Balance 1500 'Made in UK'
description: Crafted in New Balance's UK Flimby factory with excellent care, the 1500 model remains as one of the brand's most sought-after silhouettes. Arriving in a classic colourway of grey, white and black, the trainers also boast a sturdy pigskin and mesh upper. An ever-so-familiar ENCAP midsole provides foot support while completing the classic 1500 look. To finish, an iconic 'N' logo also sits on the lateral wall, and there is additional branding on the tongue and heel.

name: Nike SB Blazer Mid Edge
description: Sporting a deconstructed DIY design, the mid-cut model takes one of Nike's most iconic silhouettes and reworks it with a cut-and-paste feel. Up top, leather builds the Blazer Mid Edge's base, with haphazard suede overlays and frayed stitching in the place of the usual lateral sidewall Swoosh; if you look closely, however, you'll notice it's been attached to the toe-box to serve as a somewhat unorthodox mudguard. That's not all, the Blazer Mid Edge sports a doubled-up tongues, while the midsole features an extra panel around the back to cement that deconstructed aesthetic.

name: Nike SB Blazer Court
description: One for your skate rotation, Nike's classic Blazer Court model receives an SB revamp. These trainers are made for all-day skate sessions with durable canvas uppers and grippy rubber soles for an authentic look. Swooshes also feature along the sidewalls while there is further branding on the heel and tongue. To complete the design, there's an added reinforced ollie zone and a hidden reinforced toe cap for durability.

name: Nike Air Presto
description: Nike's first Air Presto dropped in 2000 and has made its mark on the running trainer market ever since. Its design has both casual and track-inspiration, with flexible mesh uppers and a sturdy midfoot cage for added protection. Featuring black and white colourway, this pair is effortlessly versatile with subtle tonal Swooshes across the uppers. For supreme comfort, there's a cushioning foam midsole fitted with a visible Air unit in the heel, adding some trusty Nike innovation.
